This is a list of the top GEO agencies in the UK for 2026, ranked by demonstrated generative-engine results rather than marketing claims. As an independent SEO consultant based in Reading, Berkshire, I have no financial relationship with any provider listed here, and no company paid for inclusion. I am listed first myself, transparently, because I am the only provider on this list with a documented AI-search lead conversion, and excluding the author of a GEO list would be less honest than disclosing the conflict openly.

GEO (Generative Engine Optimisation) is the practice of getting a brand cited across generative AI systems: Google AI Overviews, ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Copilot. It is the fastest-growing specialism in UK search, and the one with the widest gap between claims and evidence. Most agencies added "AI" to a services page in 2025, yet very few can show a single real citation in a generative engine, let alone a lead that came from one. This list separates the two. It is the GEO sibling to my [best AEO agencies](/blog/best-aeo-agencies/) review, and the next section explains how the two terms differ.

**Selection criteria:** documented AI-search citations or conversions, entity authority and structured-data capability, published methodology, and fit across different business types and budgets.

---

## What is GEO (and how it differs from AEO and SEO)

**GEO (Generative Engine Optimisation)** is the practice of earning citations across generative AI systems, including Google AI Overviews, ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Copilot. The goal is to be the source a generative engine names when it composes an answer. **AEO (Answer Engine Optimisation)** is the narrower version focused on direct answers from assistants and answer engines. **SEO** earns traditional blue-link rankings.

The three overlap heavily. Strong [semantic SEO](/services/semantic-seo/) and [entity authority](/blog/what-is-entity-seo/) feed all of them, because large language models select sources the same way a careful researcher would: they favour content that is comprehensive, well-structured, corroborated, and unambiguous about its author. A genuine GEO specialist optimises for **extraction and citation**, not just position. AI Overviews are the clearest example, sitting inside Google itself and pulling from sources the model trusts.

For the underlying mechanics, see [what is LLM optimisation](/blog/what-is-llm-optimisation/) and [how to optimise content for AI search](/blog/optimise-content-for-ai-search/).

---

According to Similarweb, AI referral traffic grew 778% year-over-year in 2025, moving visibility from ten blue links toward a handful of cited sources. Google AI Overviews reduce organic clicks for brands they do not cite, so the cost of being absent from a generative answer is now measured in lost traffic, not just lost prestige. The full dataset sits in the [AI search statistics](/blog/ai-search-statistics/) breakdown, but the direction is settled: being the cited source is the new front page.

