## How to Choose a GEO Agency

Most providers advertising "GEO" cannot demonstrate a single citation. These markers separate genuine generative-engine capability from a repositioned services page:

1. **A documented citation or conversion.** A screenshot of the brand named in an AI Overview, ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Copilot, ideally with a lead attached.
2. **Entity authority capability.** Understanding of how LLMs identify and trust entities. See [what is entity SEO](/blog/what-is-entity-seo/).
3. **Structured-data fluency.** The markup that helps AI crawlers extract a page accurately.
4. **A measurement method.** How they track citations and generative-engine visibility over time, not just rankings.
5. **Published methodology, not slogans.** Evidence of *how* they work, weighted above testimonials.

If your brand is missing from generative answers, start with [why your brand is not appearing in ChatGPT](/blog/brand-not-appearing-in-chatgpt/), then build the foundation with [how to build topical authority](/blog/how-to-build-topical-authority/). The discipline that applies to any SEO hire is set out in [how to choose an SEO consultant](/blog/how-to-choose-seo-consultant/).

---

## Questions to Ask Any GEO Provider

1. **"Show me a brand you have made appear in a generative answer."** A screenshot from an AI Overview, ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Copilot. No example means no proof.
2. **"How do you build and measure entity authority?"** A real answer references corroboration, structured data, and citation tracking, not just "we optimise for AI".
3. **"Is GEO a separate add-on or built into the strategy?"** Genuine GEO comes from the same content and entity foundations as good SEO; a premium standalone "AI" line item with no results is a red flag.
4. **"What changed in your method over the last six months?"** Generative search moves fast. A provider who cannot answer is not keeping up.
5. **"What do I own if we stop after three months?"** You should keep all strategy, audits, and content.

